  "rationale": "<p>The discriminant of <i>a</i><i>x</i>&sup2; + <i>b</i><i>x</i> + <i>c</i> = 0 is <i>b</i>&sup2; &minus; 4<i>a</i><i>c</i>. Here it is 6&sup2; &minus; 4(3)(11) = 36 &minus; 132 = &minus;96. A negative discriminant means there are zero distinct real solutions.</p>",
